                     <interp inst="t18211205-7-defend155" type="age" value="18"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18211205-7-off39" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18211205-7-off39" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-7-off39" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18211205-7-cd40" type="crimeDate">9th of November</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-7-off39 t18211205-7-cd40"></join>, one handkerchief, value 3 s., the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18211205-7-victim157" type="victimName">
                           Frederick 
                           Sharman
                        <interp inst="t18211205-7-victim157" type="surname" value="Sharman"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18211205-7-victim157" type="given" value="Frederick"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18211205-7-victim157" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-7-off39 t18211205-7-victim157"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>FREDERICK SHARMAN. I am a <rs id="t18211205-7-viclabel41" type="occupation">shoe factor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-7-victim157 t18211205-7-viclabel41"></join>, and live in Cammomile-street. On the 9th of November, between eleven and twelve o'clock, I was on the east side of <placeName id="t18211205-7-crimeloc42">St. Paul's church-yard</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-7-crimeloc42" type="placeName" value="St. Paul's church-yard"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-7-crimeloc42" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-7-off39 t18211205-7-crimeloc42"></join>, and saw two young men handing a handkerchief one to the other, which induced me to feel my pocket; I missed my handkerchief, the prisoner is the one who received it - I seized him, he was within two yards of me, the other went away. I asked him to let me see the handkerchief which was in his pocket, he said he had none about him - I found my handkerchief up his back, and gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-7-person158">
                  NATHANIEL 
                  MINES
               <interp inst="t18211205-7-person158" type="surname" value="MINES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-7-person158" type="given" value="NATHANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-7-person158" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was in St. Paul's church-yard, and saw Mr. Sharman there, holding the prisoner; he charged him with stealing his handkerchief, he said nothing.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked it up in the churchyard.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18211205-7-verdict43" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18211205-7-verdict43" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18211205-7-punish44" type="punishmentDescription">
